# MCP Server Ecosystem

All custom MCP servers are set up from `DevTools/CodingTools/Setup-*` folders. Each folder contains a `Setup-*.ps1`, `Test-*.ps1`, and `Uninstall-*.ps1` script.

## Quick Setup (All Servers at Once)

```powershell
pwsh.exe -NoProfile -File "C:\opt\src\DedgePsh\DevTools\CodingTools\Setup-AllMcpServers\Setup-AllMcpServers.ps1"
```

This auto-detects whether Cursor and/or Ollama is installed and runs all relevant setup and test scripts. Use `-SkipTest` to skip verification or `-SkipSetup` to only run tests.

## Cursor MCP Servers

| MCP Name | Cursor Server Name | Type | Setup Folder | Key Tool |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| RAG servers (multiple) | `user-<rag-name>` | Python stdio proxy | `Setup-RagMcpCursor` | `query_docs` |
| `db2-query` | `user-db2-query` | Streamable HTTP | `Setup-Db2QueryMcpCursor` | `query_db2` |
| `postgresql-query` | `user-postgresql-query` | Node.js stdio | `Setup-PostgreSqlMcpCursor` | `query_postgresql` |
| `autodoc-query` | `user-autodoc-query` | Streamable HTTP | `Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor` | `list_documents`, `get_document`, `search_documents` |

**Cursor prefixes all user MCP servers with `user-`.** When calling via `CallMcpTool`, always use the `user-*` name.

## MCP Server Types

### Streamable HTTP (remote)
The server runs on a remote app server (e.g. IIS). Cursor connects directly via a URL in `mcp.json`. No local process needed.

```json
{ "mcpServers": { "autodoc-query": { "url": "http://<server>/AutoDocJson/mcp" } } }
```

### Python stdio proxy (local proxy to remote)
A local Python venv creates an MCP stdio server that forwards queries over HTTP to remote Python services. The setup script creates the venv and registers it in `mcp.json`.

```json
{ "mcpServers": { "<rag-name>": { "command": "python", "args": ["server_mcp_proxy.py", ...] } } }
```

### Node.js stdio (local)
The server runs entirely on the developer machine as a Node.js stdio process. Used for databases accessible from the local network.

```json
{ "mcpServers": { "postgresql-query": { "command": "node", "args": ["<path>/postgresql-mcp-server.mjs"] } } }
```

## Ollama MCP Servers

Ollama variants register PowerShell functions (e.g. `Ask-Rag`, `Ask-Db2`, `Ask-AutoDoc`) instead of Cursor MCP entries. These are available in PowerShell sessions after setup.

| MCP Name | Setup Folder | Description |
|---|---|---|
| AutoDoc Query (Ask-AutoDoc) | `Setup-AutoDocMcpOllama` | PowerShell `Ask-AutoDoc` function for CLI doc queries |
| RAG (Ask-Rag) | `Setup-RagMcpOllama` | PowerShell `Ask-Rag` function for CLI RAG queries |
| DB2 Query (Ask-Db2) | `Setup-Db2QueryMcpOllama` | PowerShell `Ask-Db2` function for CLI DB2 queries |

## Per-Server Scripts

All scripts are under `DevTools/CodingTools/`:

| Action | RAG | DB2 Query | PostgreSQL Query | AutoDoc Query |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| Setup | `Setup-RagMcpCursor\Setup-RagMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-Db2QueryMcpCursor\Setup-Db2QueryMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-PostgreSqlMcpCursor\Setup-PostgreSqlMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor\Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor.ps1` |
| Test | `Setup-RagMcpCursor\Test-RagMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-Db2QueryMcpCursor\Test-Db2QueryMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-PostgreSqlMcpCursor\Test-PostgreSqlMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor\Test-AutoDocMcpCursor.ps1` |
| Uninstall | `Setup-RagMcpCursor\Uninstall-RagMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-Db2QueryMcpCursor\Uninstall-Db2QueryMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-PostgreSqlMcpCursor\Uninstall-PostgreSqlMcpCursor.ps1` | `Setup-AutoDocMcpCursor\Uninstall-AutoDocMcpCursor.ps1` |

All scripts write to `~/.cursor/mcp.json`. Restart Cursor after setup or uninstall.

## Naming Convention

Setup folders follow the pattern: `Setup-<Purpose>Mcp<Client>`

- `<Purpose>`: `Rag`, `Db2Query`, `PostgreSql`, `AutoDoc`
- `<Client>`: `Cursor` or `Ollama`

Each folder contains three scripts: `Setup-<Name>.ps1`, `Test-<Name>.ps1`, `Uninstall-<Name>.ps1`.

## Prerequisites

- PowerShell 7+ (`pwsh.exe`)
- Python 3.11+ (for RAG stdio proxies)
- Node.js (for PostgreSQL MCP server)
- Network access to the app server hosting remote MCP endpoints
